ISLAMABAD, Aug 7 (APP):Deputy Prime Minister Muhammad Ishaq Dar and Ahmad Attaf, the Foreign Minister of the People’s Democratic Republic of Algeria, on Wednesday agreed to strengthen their economic partnership by boosting trade and investment.
According to a message shared by Foreign Office here, the meeting took place on the sidelines of an extraordinary  Organisation of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) session in Jeddah, where both parties acknowledged the deep-rooted historic ties between their countries.
